Bukit Asam, HD Finance, Tractors: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-07-26T01:44:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/bukit-asam-hd-finance-tractors-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  fell 0.5 percent to 4,087.09.  PT HD Finance (HDFA IJ): The motorcycle and car financing
company will seek an additional 500 billion rupiah ($59 million)
of bank loans this year to help fund its business, Investor
Daily Indonesia reported, citing President Director Hariono. HD
Finance was unchanged at 225 rupiah.  PT Tambang Batubara Bukit Asam (PTBA IJ): The company’s
first-half net income rose to 1.61 trillion rupiah from 908.1
billion rupiah a year earlier, the Indonesian state-owned coal
producer said in a statement published in  Bisnis Indonesia .
Bukit Asam fell 1.4 percent to 20,900 rupiah.  PT United Tractors (UNTR IJ): The company’s heavy equipment
sales in June rose to 742 units from 617 units in May and 507
units a year earlier, it said in an e-mailed statement. United
Tractors,  Indonesia ’s largest heavy equipment seller, declined
1.8 percent to 25,250 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
